data.description: The "Mare's Nest" is a lovely 1890's equestrian property which has been home to the same family for the last 50+ years. The main house is a colonial featuring some fine original details with more recent additions of a greenhouse and a main floor bedroom wing that adds an additional kitchen, laundry and great room. There are a total of 4 fireplaces, 4 bedrooms and 5 bathrooms. The stables and a number of other outbuildings add a great deal of charm to the rolling 27 acres of lawn and pastures highlighted by the bucolic swimming pond. The heated inground pool is conveniently accessed from the great room and primary bedroom. There is a hot tub and a small pool house for storage of pool toys. The stable was home to many thoroughbred racehorses over the years and has 6 stalls and a fenced paddock. The 2 barns have 9 garage bays and lots of room for equipment storage. Conveniently situated near the village of Millerton NY and a 20 minute drive to the NY train at Wassaic.
